======================================================================
EULER CHARACTERISTIC TEST
chi = sum_{k=0}^{n-1} (-1)^k dim(Omega_k)
Verify: chi_omega == chi_betti for all tournaments
Check: Is chi universal (same for all T at given n)?
======================================================================

============================================================
n = 3, samples = 500, max_p = 2
============================================================
  Example (first tournament):
    omega_dims = {0: 3, 1: 3, 2: 1}
    bettis     = {0: 1, 1: 0, 2: 0}
    chi_omega  = 1
    chi_betti  = 1

  --- Results for n=3 ---
  Mismatches (chi_omega != chi_betti): 0/500
  chi is UNIVERSAL: False
  chi distribution:
    chi =    0:   126 / 500 ( 25.20%)
    chi =    1:   374 / 500 ( 74.80%)
  Distinct omega_dim profiles: 2
  Distinct betti profiles: 2
  Omega_dim profile distribution (k=0..2):
    (3, 3, 1): 374 times
    (3, 3, 0): 126 times

